ior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/21/02 2:31:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4461.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Good 'Ol BAH</span><hr size=1> Hey All =)<br>
<br>
Just picked me up a BAH (2.8 k on BB) and am pretty excited bout it.<br>
<br>
Recently, I've noticed that the hot 2HS/2HB has been the Windblade for obvious reasons (50/44) and the classics  Axe of Dismay/Savage Stone Axe/Tae Ew Maul/etc.<br>
<br>
How would you rank the BAH as compared to the other popular 2handers mentioned above.   Keep in mind that level of warrior using this is going to be from lvl 45 - early 50's.<br>
<br>
Obviously, Windblade is #1, rest as follows?<br>
<br>
Axe of Dismay, 44/44<br>
BAH, 40/48 + 45 lifedraw<br>
Savage Stone Axe/Tae Ew Maul, both 33/36<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=394660">Noc's Gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Lvl 44 Wood Elf Warrior! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doey@thesteelwarrior>DOEY</A> at: 11/21/02 2:39:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wubaogoldenarmz>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 293<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/21/02 2:55:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4461.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  why I like and use the halberd</span><hr size=1> It's easy to swap out with a ToD, both being 2handed.<br>
<br>
Slow from the Truncheon and Lifetap from the Halberd really help when soloing.<br>
<br>
The Halberd has good enough DPS to make soloing actually a viable alternative, when combined with a slow proc and a lifetap.<br>
<br>
Least in the low 50s it does.<br>
<br>
-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ygnirthundersson>Ygnir Thundersson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/21/02 5:03:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4461.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.oozbv.demon.nl/ygnir.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: why I like and use the halberd</span><hr size=1> don't forget the +4 magic of the BaH...<br>
<br>
BaH comes second to the 44/44 and above all the others...  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3920">Ygnir Thundersson</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Warlord<br>
7th Hammer<br>
<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
Worshipper of Tyr who unfortunately doesn't exist in this game. <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thorilan>thorilan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/21/02 10:05:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4461.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: why I like and use the halberd</span><hr size=1> how often does it seem to proc?<br>
<br>
i have a tod and a wind blade and was thinking maybe i could get a Bah and once the mob is low and running ( or standing there snared) i could switch to the bah to see about getting some life back. <br>
<br>
what i mean by how often does it proc is does it proc a lot with say a 130 dex or is it one of those weapons that never seems to proc. <br>
<br>
my FG proc all the time ( just seems like some weapons want to proc some dont)<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilerboy>pilerboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/02 6:26:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4461.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  hm</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't recommend doing that, at low health mobs die far too quickly for halberd to be remotely useful in that sense... if you're that concerned just pick up two bloodpoints for the same price as the halberd and swap out to THEM when the mob hits low health... I still wouldn't recommend that either, but I suppose you could if you really wanted to.<br>
<br>
Grendon, 64 Ogre Warlord of Rallos-Zek<br>
Bristlebane Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wubaogoldenarmz>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 298<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/02 12:16:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4461.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  seems to proc about average</span><hr size=1> Barring the occasional fight where it just goes the funk off (One fight I had it proc 7 times in about 1 minute of fighting, I thought I was bugged) ... it goes off about the same rate as any other weapon I've ever wielded with a proc.<br>
<br>
Some fights I'll be lucky get a proc. Other fights I'll get 2 or 3.<br>
<br>
My warrior's Dex is 140.<br>
<br>
Uh, I wouldn't reccommend it for a swap when mob turns to run kinda thing. It's a slow swinging 2hander. And it hits hard. So you get about 3 swings tops on a fleeing mob.<br>
<br>
Since I'm still using this to solo in the low 50s (I want to grind out some AAs with my warrior, since there really isn't crap for AA that I want with my monk), I didn't even think about getting a windblade. <br>
<br>
Would much rather have the lifetap.<br>
<br>
:-)<br>
<br>
Obviously, windblade is much better for your non-freaky-monk-who-plays-a-warrior-solo-cause-he's-weird type of warrior.<br>
<br>
-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deian222>Deian222</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/02 2:56:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4461.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: seems to proc about average</span><hr size=1> So the BAH is better than the Axe of Dismay because of the lifetap proc? They're about the same price and I'm thinking about a 2-hander, so I'd love to know. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wubaogoldenarmz>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 299<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/23/02 5:14:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4461.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  only if you plan to solo</span><hr size=1> BAH is only superior to the others in a very limited scope, in that the lifetap proc, added to the slow proc from a Truncheon of Doom makes it a more efficient soloing setup.<br>
<br>
Otherwise, I would definitely take Dismay Axe over BAH any day of the week and twice on Friday.<br>
<br>
And warrior soloing is a very limited thing. Heh.<br>
<br>
-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showPrevMessage?topicID=4461.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showNextMessage?topicID=4461.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4461.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.emailToFriend?topicID=4461.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.threadControl?topicID=4461.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4461.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4461.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesteelwarriorthearena">The Arena<option value="thesteelwarriorthebattlefield">The BattleField<option value="thesteelwarriorthebunker">The Bunker<option value="thesteelwarriorthetavern">The Tavern<option value="thesteelwarriorfrm6">The